The paper describes a practical system for Multi Touch Attribution (MTA) using a Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) and Shapley Values. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves modeling user behavior and purchase patterns, which suggests that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper is focused on developing a system for an eCommerce company, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
